Package: osmiumr
Type: Package
Title: R Bindings for the 'osmium-tool' OpenStreetMap Command Line Tool
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Mark", "Padgham", email = "mark.padgham@email.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Jochen", "Topf", email = "jochen@topf.org", role = c("aut", "cph"),
           comment = "Author of the vendored osmium-tool C++ sources"))
Description: Provides R functions wrapping the command implementations of
    'osmium-tool' (<https://osmcode.org/osmium-tool/>), a command line tool
    for working with OpenStreetMap data built on the 'libosmium' library.
    Rather than shelling out to a separately installed 'osmium' binary,
    the relevant 'osmium-tool' C++ command sources are compiled directly
    into this package and called in-process through a small 'Rcpp' bridge.
License: GPL (>= 3) + file LICENSE.txt
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
SystemRequirements: C++17, libosmium (>= 2.23.1), protozero (>= 1.6.3),
    nlohmann-json (>= 3.0), boost-program-options (>= 1.55), bz2lib, zlib,
    expat, cmake. Optionally lz4 for LZ4 PBF compression support.
Imports:
    Rcpp,
    jsonlite
LinkingTo:
    Rcpp
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
